{{Year in Sri Lanka|1999}}

The following lists events that happened during '''[[1999]] in [[Sri Lanka]]'''.

==Incumbents==
*[[President of Sri Lanka|President]]: [[Chandrika Kumaratunga]].

==Events==
* On 16 November 1999, the fourth official presidential elections of Sri Lanka take place. Chandrika Kumaratunga, wins by a 51.12% margin amidst several assassination attempts prior to the campaign.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://psephos.adam-carr.net/countries/s/srilanka/srilankapres1999.txt|title=REPUBLIC OF SRI LANKA PRESIDENTIAL ELECTIONS OF 22 DECEMBER 1999|publisher=Psephos - Adam Carr's Election Archive}}
</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.manthree.com/elections/results/?id=7|title=1999 - Presidential Election|publisher=Manthree.com|access-date=2015-08-12|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140928123933/http://www.manthree.com/elections/results/?id=7|archive-date=2014-09-28|dead-url=yes|df=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.lankanewspapers.com/news/election/presidential1999.jsp|title=1999 Sri Lanka Presidential Election Results|publisher=LankaNewspapers.com}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.slelections.gov.lk/pdf/1999%20Presidential.pdf |archive-url=https://wayback.archive-it.org/all/20090304101308/http://www.slelections.gov.lk/pdf/1999%20Presidential.pdf |dead-url=yes |archive-date=2009-03-04 |title=Result of Presidential Election 1999 |publisher=Department of Elections, Sri Lanka |access-date=2015-08-12 |df= }}</ref><!-- These are the sources to prove that Chandrika won the elections --> 
* In October 1999 the Oddusuddan offensive took place, it was a military operation in which the [[LTTE|Tamil Tigers]] captured [[Oddusuddan]] from the [[Sri Lankan Army]]. The Tamil Tigers are believed to have captured large amounts of weapons & ammunitions as well as armoured vehicles in this operation.<ref name="tamilnet1999">{{cite news |first= |last= |title=Tigers raise flag at Oddusuddan|url=http://www.tamilnet.com/art.html?catid=13&artid=4153|work=TamilNet|date=1999-11-02|accessdate=2009-01-02}}</ref>

